N2  - The influences of both manipulated enrichment informational cues and individual differences on subjective job perceptions were examined. Results indicate that both the manipulation and individual differences contributed statistically and practically significant variance in the prediction of subjective job perceptions. The implications of these results for job design research are discussed.
