T1  - Job Attitudes and Organizational Performance Under Employee Ownership
AU  - Long, Richard J.
Y1  - 1980/12/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255559
DO  - 10.5465/255559
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 726
EP  - 737
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper assesses the apparent effects on job attitudes and organizational performance of recent conversions to employee ownership at three firms. Favorable effects were most evident at the firm with the highest employee ownership and least evident at the firm with the lowest. The concept of employee participation in decision making is believed to play a key role in these outcomes.
AB  - This paper assesses the apparent effects on job attitudes and organizational performance of recent conversions to employee ownership at three firms. Favorable effects were most evident at the firm with the highest employee ownership and least evident at the firm with the lowest. The concept of employee participation in decision making is believed to play a key role in these outcomes.
