TY  - JOUR
T1  - Some Alternative Definitions of Size
AU  - Gupta, Nina
Y1  - 1980/12/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255562
DO  - 10.5465/255562
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 759
EP  - 766
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a number of definitions of organizational size. According to the author, there are three perspectives related to the definition of organizational size. They include the cycles, the energic and the components approaches. The author notes that the cycles approach discusses size as a structural characteristic of an organization. The energic approach concerns itself with both human and material resources used by organizations. According to the author, the components approach takes its definition of size from common usage and tradition.
AB  - The article discusses a number of definitions of organizational size. According to the author, there are three perspectives related to the definition of organizational size. They include the cycles, the energic and the components approaches. The author notes that the cycles approach discusses size as a structural characteristic of an organization. The energic approach concerns itself with both human and material resources used by organizations. According to the author, the components approach takes its definition of size from common usage and tradition.
