T1  - The Convergent and Discriminant Validities between the IOR and the JDI: English and Spanish Forms
AU  - McCabe, Dennis J.
AU  - Dalessio, Anthony
AU  - Briga, Jānis
AU  - Sasaki, Julio
Y1  - 1980/12/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255565
DO  - 10.5465/255565
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 778
EP  - 786
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the merits of two instruments designed to determine levels of job satisfaction, the Job Descriptive Index (JDI) and the Index of Organizational Reactions (IOR). According to the author the purpose of this study is to determine whether or not responses to the Spanish forms of the two instruments were equivalent to those elicited by the English versions. The results of the study indicate that the instruments were successfully translated into Spanish, though the author believes future research should look to discover if both versions are similarly related in regards to employee turnover.
AB  - The article discusses the merits of two instruments designed to determine levels of job satisfaction, the Job Descriptive Index (JDI) and the Index of Organizational Reactions (IOR). According to the author the purpose of this study is to determine whether or not responses to the Spanish forms of the two instruments were equivalent to those elicited by the English versions. The results of the study indicate that the instruments were successfully translated into Spanish, though the author believes future research should look to discover if both versions are similarly related in regards to employee turnover.
