N2  - A model predicting relationships among individual, task design, and leader behavior variables was examined for 171 employees of a large manufacturing firm. Correlational analyses revealed significant relationships among variables and facets of satisfaction, but not productivity. Cross-lagged correlational analysis also yielded some support for the model in terms of both satisfaction and productivity.
